constant                             command                            constant

NAME
     ccoonnssttaanntt - define a constant global symbol

SYNOPSIS

     ccoonnssttaanntt ssyymmbbooll vvaalluuee

DESCRIPTION

     The ccoonnssttaanntt command creates (or modifies the value of an existing) global
     variable.  The value of a ccoonnssttaanntt global variable cannot be changed by
     ordinary assignment.  An attempt to so results in an error.

     The purpose of the ccoonnssttaanntt variable type is to prevent accidental or
     casual modification of important parameters.

EXAMPLE

     ccoonnssttaanntt EEPPOOCCHH ttiimmee(())

